# Meeneo — HearstVault dApp

## Stack
- Next.js 16 (App Router) + React 19 + TypeScript 5
- Tailwind CSS 4 (PostCSS) — design tokens in `globals.css`
- Web3: Wagmi v2, AppKit/Reown v1.8, Viem v2, Ethers v6
- Charts: Recharts v3
- State: TanStack Query v5
- Deploy: Vercel (standalone output) — CI via GitHub Actions
- Network: Base Mainnet (8453) + Base Sepolia (84532)

## Architecture
- `src/app/` — Next.js App Router pages
- `src/components/` — React components (functional only)
- `src/components/ui/` — Reusable UI primitives
- `src/hooks/` — Custom React hooks
- `src/config/` — Env, wagmi, contracts, products, mock-data
- `src/contracts/` — ABI JSON files
- `src/types/` — TypeScript type definitions
- `src/lib/` — Utilities and API clients
- `src/context/` — React Context providers

## Conventions
- Imports: use `@/*` alias → `./src/*`
- Components: functional + named exports, colocated styles
- Hooks: prefix `use`, one concern per hook
- No `any` — use proper types from `src/types/`
- Error handling: always log with context, never swallow errors
- Mock-first: all data flows support mock fallback

## Web3 Rules
- Contract addresses in `src/config/contracts.ts` — never hardcode
- Chain config in `src/config/wagmi.ts`
- Use Viem for read, Wagmi hooks for reactive state
- Always validate network before transactions (NetworkValidator)

## Styling
- Tailwind utility classes — no inline styles
- Design tokens: `--hearst-*` CSS variables in `globals.css`
- Color scale: green (#96EA7A), dark backgrounds
- Spacing: 8px base system

## Language
- Code: English (variables, comments, commits)
- User-facing: English
- Dev communication: French
